What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Xerosis Treatment Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Xerosis Treatment Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the xerosis treatment will exhibit a CAGR of around 5.25% for the forecast period of 2021-2028. Growing demand for targeted mode of therapies, surge in the research and development activities for the development of novel drugs and therapies, high prevalence of skin disorders and increased expenditure for the development of healthcare infrastructure are the major factors attributable to the growth of xerosis treatment market.

Xerosis is a condition of skin dryness. Therefore, xerosis treatment is sued for the dermatological complications in an individual. Xerosis worsens in areas where there is low humidity. It is caused by moisture deficiency. It is the most prevalent in geriatric population.

Growing prevalence of diabetes globally coupled with ever-rising geriatric population is a major factor fostering the growth of the market. Rising expenditure on the development of healthcare infrastructure, rising awareness about xerosis and its treatments and upsurge in the strategic collaboration rate among the market players are other factors also fostering the growth of the market. Increasing personal disposable income coupled with rising climatic changes is other indirect determinant that will create lucrative market growth opportunities.

However, presence of ineffective fake products in the market and unfavourable reimbursement scenario in the developing and under developed economies will pose a major challenge to the market growth. Also, high costs associated with research and development proficiencies and pricing pressure among the major manufacturers will further derail the market growth rate. Large number of low quality players in the market will also hamper the market growth rate.

